WEBVTT

1
00:02:41.694 --> 00:02:46.281
- Quack, quack.
- Look out!

2
00:02:46.449 --> 00:02:48.700
He singed my tail feathers.

3
00:02:49.786 --> 00:02:50.994
Yee-ha!

4
00:02:55.416 --> 00:02:57.251
All right, Buzz. That's enough of that.

5
00:03:01.923 --> 00:03:04.258
What did I just say?

6
00:03:04.592 --> 00:03:06.802
That is a good way to lose an eye, my friend.

7
00:03:07.387 --> 00:03:09.638
Hold it. We've got company at two o'clock.

8
00:03:10.306 --> 00:03:11.557
I got him, Mailman. Hang on.

9
00:03:13.101 --> 00:03:14.935
Here we go.

10
00:03:17.230 --> 00:03:20.357
- Buzz, what is goin' on up there?
- Just movin' a road hog.

11
00:03:24.612 --> 00:03:27.906
- Knock it off! What kind of stunt was that?
- Just seein' what this baby can do.

12
00:03:30.869 --> 00:03:33.245
This bag of bones isn't rated past Mach two.

13
00:03:34.455 --> 00:03:38.375
- Mach one!
- The G-forces, Buzz! The G-forces!

14
00:03:38.543 --> 00:03:40.627
Mach two! Gotta push the envelope.

15
00:03:42.338 --> 00:03:44.214
Mach three!

16
00:03:44.799 --> 00:03:46.967
Buzz! We're tearing apart!

17
00:03:49.554 --> 00:03:53.557
I'm losin' control.
Eject, Mailman. Hit the silk!

18
00:03:55.059 --> 00:03:57.811
- I can't get out!
- What are you doing?

19
00:03:58.479 --> 00:04:00.564
Buzz! Get back here!

20
00:04:01.107 --> 00:04:03.650
OK. I've been in tougher scrapes than this.

21
00:04:03.776 --> 00:04:07.112
There's the ground. It looks hard. OK, trees.

22
00:04:07.238 --> 00:04:09.406
No! Oh. Mahogany. Ow!

23
00:04:09.490 --> 00:04:11.742
Squirrel's nest. Bird. Ow! Pine.

24
00:04:11.826 --> 00:04:13.493
Ow! Oh, the ground.

25
00:04:14.162 --> 00:04:16.204
Oh... Oh...

26
00:04:16.289 --> 00:04:18.832
Oh, I made it.

27
00:04:18.958 --> 00:04:22.002
I made it! There is a God.

28
00:04:22.670 --> 00:04:24.671
Hallelujaaaaaa!

29
00:04:24.881 --> 00:04:29.217
Ow! Oh! Ouch! Ow!

30
00:04:33.014 --> 00:04:35.515
Oh, you're French, aren't you?

31
00:04:35.642 --> 00:04:37.684
Ah... yeah, just like that.

32
00:04:56.955 --> 00:04:59.039
- Hey, look! There's one!
- Uh-oh.

33
00:05:51.592 --> 00:05:53.802
Topper Harley?

34
00:05:54.137 --> 00:05:56.096
Once, perhaps.

35
00:05:56.180 --> 00:05:58.098
Now I am called Tukachinchilla.

36
00:05:58.933 --> 00:06:01.393
- What does it mean?
- Fluffy Bunny Feet.

37
00:06:04.564 --> 00:06:06.356
It's very nice.

38
00:06:06.482 --> 00:06:08.608
I'm Lieutenant Commander James Block.

39
00:06:08.735 --> 00:06:09.943
I knew your father Buzz.

40
00:06:12.238 --> 00:06:14.531
Until his incident, he was
the greatest pilot who ever lived.

41
00:06:17.785 --> 00:06:19.036
We need to talk.

42
00:06:32.300 --> 00:06:33.800
The Navy wants...

43
00:06:41.267 --> 00:06:42.476
The Navy wants you back, Harley.

44
00:06:43.561 --> 00:06:46.646
They threw me out. Why should I go back?

45
00:06:47.607 --> 00:06:50.942
I came here to get away from the Navy.
Away from flying.

46
00:07:05.750 --> 00:07:09.086
The Navy has
a top-secret mission: Sleepy Weasel.

47
00:07:09.170 --> 00:07:12.255
I'm giving you a second chance,
which your father never had.

48
00:07:12.340 --> 00:07:14.466
You're the best of the best, Topper.

49
00:07:17.011 --> 00:07:22.015
Leave me to speak with the
one. He is wise in the ways of such things.

50
00:07:26.395 --> 00:07:27.979
The Navy really needs you.

51
00:07:28.606 --> 00:07:29.981
Great helium!

52
